# SDD workflow (Skillgrid)

## Read project context first

For every `/sdd-*` phase **except** `/sdd-init`, follow `.agents/rules/skillgrid-context-contract.mdc` for `CONTEXT.md` reads, glossary conflicts, and updates.

## Phase intent (do not skip silently)

Use the named command that matches the phase. Rough dependency shape:

`proposal → specs → design → tasks → apply → verify → archive` (with `explore` / `brainstorm` / `loop` as entry or continuation paths per `docs/04-commands.md`).

## OpenSpec change layout (typical)

- `openspec/changes/<change-id>/proposal.md`
- `openspec/changes/<change-id>/design.md`
- `openspec/changes/<change-id>/tasks.md`
- `openspec/changes/<change-id>/specs/**/spec.md`

## Handoff triple (visibility outside chat)

- `.skillgrid/tasks/context_<change-id>.md`
- `.skillgrid/tasks/events/<change-id>.jsonl`
- `.skillgrid/tasks/research/<change-id>/`

Follow `.agents/skills/_shared/skillgrid-handoff.md` when updating board or phase state.

## Init and persistence

Respect the project’s artifact store mode (`engram` / `openspec` / `hybrid` / `none`). When Engram backs artifacts, **`mem_search` previews are truncated** — use `mem_get_observation` for full content before relying on requirement text.

